content:
Here is an example of how the code for the feedback feature and post-use instructions for farmers might look like:
```javascript
// Feedback Feature

// Create a function to display a feedback form
function showFeedbackForm() {
  // Code to display the form
}

// Create a function to submit feedback
function submitFeedback() {
  // Code to submit feedback to the database
}

// Add an event listener to the feedback button to show the form
document.getElementById("feedback-btn").addEventListener("click", showFeedbackForm);

// Add an event listener to the submit button on the feedback form to submit feedback
document.getElementById("submit-btn").addEventListener("click", submitFeedback);
// Post-Use Instructions

// Create a function to display post-use instructions
function showInstructions() {
  // Code to display instructions
}

// Add an event listener to the "next" button on the AR experience to display instructions
document.getElementById("next-btn").addEventListener("click", showInstructions);
```
In this example, the feedback feature includes a function to display a feedback form and another function to submit the feedback to the database. The event listeners are added to the appropriate buttons to trigger these functions.

The post-use instructions feature includes a function to display the instructions and an event listener to trigger the function when the "next" button on the AR experience is clicked.
